title: Jennifer Hawkins shares adorable pictures of her newborn alongside husband Jake Wall
text:
Supermodel Jennifer Hawkins has shared some adorable images of her first child with husband Jake Wall.

The former Miss Universe gave birth to her daughter Frankie Violet last week and has been infatuated with her new bub as she recovers at Sydney's Mater Hospital.

On Wednesday, the 35-year-old mum gave a touching tribute to hospital staff alongside a picture of her tiny newborn.

'Those feet' Jennifer Hawkins uploaded a picture of her newborn daughter Frankie Violet along with a touching message for the hospital staff

'A big thank you to the entire team at the Mater Hospital!' Jennifer said.

'The whole maternity ward and midwives were so incredible, we can't thank you enough! We had a beautiful experience,' she added.

The supermodel also posted some adorable photos with her parents Gail and Bob Hawkins.

Both proud grandparents held the newborn in their hands.

Our one and only: The former miss universe has been infatuated with her tiny bub since the birth last week

Doting dad and property developer Jake uploaded a picture of the two together not long after the birth .

'Welcome to the world Frankie Violet. Our hearts are full,' he gushed on Instagram.

Jennifer and Jake first announced they were expecting a child back in May.

It brings back memories: Proud grandparents Gail (left) and Bob Hawkins (right) were only pictured holding their new grandchild

At the time, they shared the same photo of Jennifer showing off her baby bump to their respective Instagram accounts.

'I'm so happy to share with you some exciting news! Jake and I are expecting a baby girl! We can't wait to meet her!' Jennifer wrote.

'Thank you to our beautiful family and friends for their love and support and, most importantly, to my hubby Jake – I can't wait to see you as a daddy!'
description: Jennifer Hawkins gave birth to her daughter Frankie Violet alongside husband Jake Wall last week in Mater Hospital in Sydney and the couple have been infatuated with their bub.
authors: Tom Place For Daily Mail Australia
